** About the Company **   
  
Davidson Technology are currently supporting a State Government Authority in
their pursuit of a highly skilled Web Developer on an initial 6-month
contract.  
  
  
  
  
** About the Role **   
  
As the Web Developer, you will be responsible for designing, developing,
implementing, and maintaining websites, online forms, multimedia, web
applications, and collaboration sites that adhere to publication, branding,
and security guidelines while meeting Queensland Government standards. You'll
support the maintenance of content management systems like Squiz Matrix,
WordPress, and Drupal, by updating content, developing templates, and managing
CMS configuration. Collaborating with staff, you will provide technical
advice, manage projects, and ensure high-level ease-of-use for customers.
You'll liaise with ICT units, manage front-end design, produce web metrics
reports, optimise resource discovery, and stay updated on web standards and
trends while supporting the development of standards and policies. This role
requires both autonomous work and collaboration within a team.  
  
  
  
  
** About You **   
  
To be successful, you will possess experience in designing and managing web
content, ideally on platforms such as Squiz Matrix, WordPress, and Drupal,
along with expertise in developing content strategy, information architecture,
and navigation. Additionally, you should demonstrate familiarity with user-
centred design, web standards, accessibility, and stakeholder market testing.
Previous experience in a Government setting, whether local, state, or Federal,
is preferred.  
  
  
  
  
** The Benefits **   
  
You will be offered an excellent hourly rate for the duration of the 6-month
contract starting ASAP.  
  
  
  
  
